                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.042,
                                "byte_start": 87609,
                                "byte_stop": 127838,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 01-408 Holmes Group, Inc. versus Vornado Air Circulation Systems will be announced by Justice Scalia."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.042,
                        "stop": 270.628,
                        "byte_start": 127838,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.042,
                                "stop": 15.445,
                                "byte_start": 127838,
                                "byte_stop": 149467,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.445,
                                "stop": 20.746,
                                "byte_start": 149467,
                                "byte_stop": 170678,
                                "text": "It involves a rather technical question concerning the jurisdiction of that court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.746,
                                "stop": 35.055,
                                "byte_start": 170678,
                                "byte_stop": 227834,
                                "text": "Petitioner filed a Federal Court action seeking a declaratory judgment that its products did not infringe respondent\u2019s trade dress and in an injunction restraining respondent from accusing it of such infringement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.055,
                                "stop": 41.722,
                                "byte_start": 227834,
                                "byte_stop": 254584,
                                "text": "Respondent\u2019s answer asserted a compulsory patent infringement counterclaim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.722,
                                "stop": 45.289,
                                "byte_start": 254584,
                                "byte_stop": 268794,
                                "text": "The District Court ruled in favor of the petitioner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.289,
                                "stop": 53.54,
                                "byte_start": 268794,
                                "byte_stop": 301813,
                                "text": "Respondent then appealed to the Federal Circuit instead of the Regional Court of Appeals, which in this case would have been the Tenth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.54,
                                "stop": 62.235,
                                "byte_start": 301813,
                                "byte_stop": 336608,
                                "text": "The Federal Circuit, notwithstanding the petitioner\u2019s challenge to its jurisdiction, vacated the District Court\u2019s judgment and remanded the case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.235,
                                "stop": 71.245,
                                "byte_start": 336608,
                                "byte_stop": 372657,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari and now vacate and remand with instructions to transfer this case to the Court of Appeals to the Tenth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.245,
                                "stop": 94.52,
                                "byte_start": 372657,
                                "byte_stop": 465758,
                                "text": "Pursuant to 28 U.S.C. Section 1295(a)(1), the Federal Circuit has exclusive jurisdiction over \u201can appeal from a final decision of a District Court of the United States if the jurisdiction of that court was based in whole or in part on 28 U.S.C. Section 1338."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.52,
                                "stop": 111.23,
                                "byte_start": 465758,
                                "byte_stop": 532631,
                                "text": "28 U.S.C. Section 1338(a) gives District Courts jurisdiction over civil actions \u201carising under\u0022, magic words to lawyers, \u0022arising under federal patent law.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.23,
                                "stop": 125.149,
                                "byte_start": 532631,
                                "byte_stop": 588220,
                                "text": "Because 1338(a) uses the same operative language, arising under, as 28 U.S.C. Section 1331 which confers general federal question jurisdiction on the District Courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.149,
                                "stop": 141.561,
                                "byte_start": 588220,
                                "byte_stop": 653944,
                                "text": "We held in a case called Christianson versus Colt Industries Operating Corporation that the well-pleaded complaint rule governing whether a case arises under 1331 also governs whether a case arises under Section 1338(a)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.561,
                                "stop": 154.225,
                                "byte_start": 653944,
                                "byte_stop": 704517,
                                "text": "As adapted to Section 1338(a), that well-pleaded complaint rule provides that whether a case arises under patent law is determined by what appears in the plaintiff\u2019s well-pleaded complaint."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.225,
                                "stop": 157.757,
                                "byte_start": 704517,
                                "byte_stop": 718727,
                                "text": "That is a complaint that does not have surplus agenda."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.757,
                                "stop": 170.02,
                                "byte_start": 718727,
                                "byte_stop": 767733,
                                "text": "Because petitioner\u2019s well-pleaded complaint asserted no claim arising under federal patent law but just the trade dress claim, the Federal Circuit erred in asserting jurisdiction over this appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.02,
                                "stop": 180.156,
                                "byte_start": 767733,
                                "byte_stop": 808275,
                                "text": "We are not persuaded by respondent\u2019s argument that the well-pleaded complaint rule allows a counterclaim to serve as the basis for a District Courts arising under jurisdiction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.156,
                                "stop": 189.802,
                                "byte_start": 808275,
                                "byte_stop": 846832,
                                "text": "To accept this argument would contravene the face of the complaint principle set forth in our prior cases and the long standing policies furthered by that principle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.802,
                                "stop": 197.204,
                                "byte_start": 846832,
                                "byte_stop": 876507,
                                "text": "It would leave acceptance or rejection of a State Forum to the master of the counterclaim rather than to the plaintiff."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.204,
                                "stop": 207.823,
                                "byte_start": 876507,
                                "byte_stop": 918930,
                                "text": "It would radically expand the class of removable cases, and it would undermine the clarity and ease of administration of the well-pleaded complaint doctrine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.823,
                                "stop": 230.791,
                                "byte_start": 918930,
                                "byte_stop": 1010776,
                                "text": "We are also not persuaded by respondent\u2019s alternative argument that reading Section 1295(a)(1) and Section 1338(a) to confer appellate jurisdiction on the Federal Circuit whenever a patent law counterclaim is raised is necessary to effect congress\u2019 goal of promoting patent law uniformity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 230.791,
                                "stop": 239.375,
                                "byte_start": 1010776,
                                "byte_stop": 1045153,
                                "text": "This Court\u2019s task is not to determine what would further congress\u2019 goal but to determine what the statute\u2019s words must fairly be understood to mean."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.375,
                                "stop": 259.072,
                                "byte_start": 1045153,
                                "byte_stop": 1123939,
                                "text": "It would be impossible to say that section 1338(a)\u2019s arising under language means the well-pleaded complaint rule when read on its own, but means respondent\u2019s complaint or counterclaim rule when it is referred to by Section 1295(a)(1)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.072,
                                "stop": 270.628,
                                "byte_start": 1123939,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment; Justice Ginsburg has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in which Justice O\u2019Connor has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
